# 📚 What I Learned

- Writing Bash scripts using `#!/bin/bash`
- Using `grep` to search for specific patterns in log files
- Counting matching lines with `grep -c`
- Counting total lines using `wc -l`
- Displaying the last lines of a file using `tail`
- Reading and analyzing log files
- Using shell commands together to generate reports
- Redirecting command output to a file using `>`
- Creating and executing shell scripts with `chmod +x`
- Running Bash scripts from the Ubuntu (WSL) terminal
- Organizing Linux projects with a proper folder structure
- Version control using Git
- Pushing projects to GitHub
